transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Edgar, how can I help you today?

Speaker 2: Yes, sir.

Speaker 1: I'm calling up, uh, I ordered, uh, some of the radio,

Speaker 2: like, new stuff, not the stuff that they sent me.

Speaker 1: I'm a little confused.

Speaker 2: You wanted to confirm what you received?

Speaker 1: What's your last name and a zip code?

Speaker 2: Well, the zip code's 27962.

Speaker 1: What I received was cited as a-

Speaker 2: Well, no, hold on.

Speaker 1: No, I needed your last name and a zip code, sir.

Speaker 2: You didn't give me the information I needed.

Speaker 1: Last name's Sousa, S-O-U-S-E-A.

Speaker 2: Yeah, let me pull this up first,

Speaker 1: then you can continue from there,

Speaker 2: because I need to see what's going on.

Speaker 1: Okay, so you ordered the AG Viagra.

Speaker 2: What did you receive?

Speaker 1: What is the marking on the pill?

Speaker 2: Not the bottle, or-

Speaker 1: It's some generic stuff.

Speaker 2: Yeah, yeah, yeah.

Speaker 1: So what does the marking on the pill say?

Speaker 2: The markings on the pill?

Speaker 1: Yes.

Speaker 2: Sometimes they just give me a headache, man,

Speaker 1: because they don't do nothing for me.

Speaker 2: It says AC340.

Speaker 1: Got it.

Speaker 2: So I can validate that that's the wrong one.

Speaker 1: The only marking you should have seen there is 100.

Speaker 2: Yeah.

Speaker 1: I'm going to notify my pharmacy.

Speaker 2: They'll ship you a brand new order out.

Speaker 1: You'll receive that in about three to four business days.

Speaker 2: Regarding the one you have,

Speaker 1: you could just hold on to that or dispose of that,

Speaker 2: but we'll send you the correct one.

Speaker 1: And this is the new Viagra, right?

Speaker 2: Yeah, the one we're going to ship you is the new one.

Speaker 1: It's going to have 100 on the pill instead of AC.

Speaker 2: Yeah, that's what I'm saying.

Speaker 1: This is generic.

Speaker 2: They ain't doing what they're supposed to be doing.

Speaker 1: Yeah, no worries.

Speaker 2: I'll notify the pharmacy to ship you a new one,

Speaker 1: and you'll get that in a few days.

Speaker 2: If any questions come up, let us know.

Speaker 1: Hope you have a great day.

Speaker 2: Okay, thank you.

Speaker 1: No worries.

Speaker 2: Bye-bye.
